The player should be able to do the following: 

have a opening menu, where they can click start game
- this way we can add more features in the future

have a level selection, there should be 4 button: 
- tutorial (which will be implemented first)
- campaign (pre written levels, which will be implemented second) 
- ascension (the main way to play the game, which will be the final product)
- Vs a friend, where the player can either join a room or create a room. this will be used for 1v1, (this will be added somewhere along the production)

In tutorial: 
- the character is picked for the player, which is chess. there will be instructions on how to play. 

In campaign, the player can pick a campaign which will have the pre made levels with choosen character and map

In ascension, the player can pick a character (ie, chess, shogi, xiangqi, etc) and a map will be generated

In an enemy level: 
    - the player have a branching of rooms, where it branches out and back into one at the boss. 
    - each room the enemy will roll a number, and their roll will be up to the enemy type that they are. 
    - The player get their 1 minimal move + the move they roll to drop pieces into formation. 
    - the player will have a preview on the enemy formation. 

In an blacksmith level: 
    - the player can buy/sell equipements
    - there will also be currency dropped from enemies
    - They can change the equipments on their units

In an supply site: 
    - the player can buy/exchange different troops
    - the player can change equipments on their units
    - the player can recover an amount of captures

In a boss level: 
    - the player should encounter a boss

